	 <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545"> 
		<head altrender="biography" id="a2">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head> 
		<p>Professor in the Dept. of Human Development (1966-1993) and Director
		  of the Center for Research on the Effects of Television.</p> 
		 <p> Condry graduated from West Virigina University with an A.B. degree in 1961 and 
		 an M.A. in 1962.  He received his PhD in social psychology in 1966 from the 
		 University of California at Los Angeles.  His entire teaching career was spent 
		 at Cornell with sabbaticals at the University of Kansas and at Stanford University.</p> 
	 </bioghist> 
	 <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520"> 
		<head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head> 
		<p>Includes publications and papers written by Condry concerning his
		  research on the psychology of television and its impact on children.</p> 
	 </scopecontent> 
